public class Calculator {
    public static int add(int a, int b) {
        return a + b;
    }
}
In this example, the Calculator class has a static method called add that takes two integer parameters a and b. The method performs the addition operation and returns the result.

To summarize, constructors are special methods used for object initialization, whereas methods are blocks of code that perform specific tasks or actions. Constructors are called automatically when objects are created, while methods are explicitly called. Constructors have the same name as the class and don't have a return type, while methods have a return type (or void) and can accept parameters.
